Your points are valid and highlight some common misconceptions about time dilation and the perception of time in relativity. Let‚Äôs delve deeper into these concepts to clarify the distinction between the actual passage of time and the perception of time based on relative motion and gravitational effects.

Special Relativity: Understanding Time Dilation
Relative Motion and Time Dilation:

In special relativity, time dilation occurs due to relative motion between two observers.
The time dilation effect is given by the Lorentz factor:
